This paper focuses on a technique for tracking Java methods in Git repositories, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed technique, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), or databases (cs.DB) depending on the specific methods used.
